    <h2>About Sandy Nicholson</h2>
 

  <p>Growing up in Australia, Sandy collected lizards and snakes.  He dreamed of becoming a herpetologist and having his own reptile park. When he abandoned the herpetology dream, Sandy turned to photography. He found that photographs were easier to store  and look after than spiders.</p>

<p>He has worked for the Financial Times Magazine, Wired, Saturday Night Magazine, and People.</p>

<p>Sandy's photographs have exhibited at the National Portrait Gallery, London, the World Expo, Lisbon, Fotofeis, Scotland and the Museum of Contemporary Art, Sydney.</p>

<p>Sandy now lives in Toronto, Canada.</p>

